联邦调查局探员承认自己的所作所为是荒谬的。

87
00:04:06.807 --> 00:04:10.036
A federal judge doesn't want you to hear about these conversations.
一位联邦法官不想公开这些谈话。

88
00:04:10.036 --> 00:04:13.187
He sealed the transcripts and placed them under a protective order
他将谈话记录封存，严加看管，

89
00:04:13.187 --> 00:04:16.604
in an attempt to prevent someone like me from doing something like this.
防止像我这样的人将其公之于众。

90
00:04:17.394 --> 00:04:19.405
Behind closed doors, the lead agent,
私底下，这名领头的探员，

91
00:04:19.405 --> 00:04:20.736
the squad supervisor,
小队队长，

92
00:04:20.736 --> 00:04:22.371
described their would-be terrorist
将这些未来的”恐怖分子“，

93
00:04:22.371 --> 00:04:25.002
as a "retarded fool who didn't have a pot to piss in."
描述为“穷困潦倒的弱智傻瓜”。

94
00:04:25.002 --> 00:04:26.829
They described his terrorist ambitions
将他的恐怖主义目标

95
00:04:26.829 --> 00:04:30.818
as wishy-washy and a pipe dream scenario.
描述为微不足道、白日做梦。

96
00:04:30.818 --> 00:04:32.576
But that didn't stop the FBI.
但联邦调查局没有罢手。

97
00:04:32.576 --> 00:04:35.912
They provided Sami Osmakac everything he needed.
他们为萨米·奥斯马卡什提供所需的一切。

98
00:04:35.912 --> 00:04:39.624
They gave him a car bomb, they gave him an AK-47,
汽车炸弹，AK-47，

99
00:04:39.624 --> 00:04:42.206
they helped him make a so-called martyrdom video,
帮他录制了一段所谓的“殉难”视频，

100
00:04:42.206 --> 00:04:44.300
and they even gave him money for a taxi cab
甚至给他付了出租车钱，

101
00:04:44.300 --> 00:04:46.764
so that he could get to where they wanted him to go.
送他前往选定的目标地点。

102
00:04:47.824 --> 00:04:49.634
As they were working the sting,
在设计整个圈套的过程中，

103
00:04:49.634 --> 00:04:53.147
the squad supervisor tells his agents he wanted a Hollywood ending.
小队队长告诉探员们，他想要一个好莱坞（电影）式的结尾。

104
00:04:54.347 --> 00:04:55.988
And he got a Hollywood ending.
结果他如愿以偿了。

105
00:04:56.868 --> 00:04:59.429
When Sami Osmakac attempted to deliver what he thought
当萨米·奥斯马卡什试图将汽车炸弹

106
00:04:59.429 --> 00:05:00.725
was a car bomb,
运送到位时，

107
00:05:00.725 --> 00:05:04.404
he was arrested, convicted and  sentenced to 40 years in prison.
他被抓了，判入狱40年。

108
00:05:05.424 --> 00:05:08.043
Sami Osmakac isn't alone.
萨米·奥斯马卡什并不是特例。

109
00:05:08.043 --> 00:05:10.645
He's one of more than  175 so-called terrorists,
他只是这超过175名所谓的“恐怖分子”中的一员，

110
00:05:10.645 --> 00:05:13.623
for whom the FBI has created  Hollywood endings.
联邦调查局给他们编造了一个好莱坞（电影）式的结尾。

111
00:05:15.633 --> 00:05:18.332
U.S. government officials call this the War on Terror.
美国政府官方所谓的“反恐战争”，

112
00:05:18.802 --> 00:05:20.579
It's really just theater,
其实只是一场戏，

113
00:05:20.579 --> 00:05:22.909
a national security theater,
一场国家安全的大戏，

114
00:05:22.909 --> 00:05:25.394
with mentally ill men like Sami Osmakac
由萨米·奥斯马卡什这样的精神病人，

115
00:05:25.394 --> 00:05:28.441
unwitting actors in a  carefully choreographed production
在毫不知情的情况下出演，而剧本由联邦调查局

116
00:05:28.441 --> 00:05:30.649
brought to you by the FBI.
精心编写，并呈献给大家。

117
00:05:30.649 --> 00:05:31.776
Thank you.
谢谢。

118
00:05:31.776 --> 00:05:34.690
(Applause)
（掌声）

119
00:05:40.910 --> 00:05:44.241
Tom Rielly: So, those are some pretty strong accusations,
汤姆·雷利（TR）：这些指控非常严重，

120
00:05:44.241 --> 00:05:45.758
pretty strong charges.
罪名很大。

121
00:05:46.918 --> 00:05:48.531
How can you back this up?
你有什么依据吗？

122
00:05:48.531 --> 00:05:50.547
Trevor Aaronson: My research began in 2010
特雷弗·阿伦森（TA）：我的研究开始于2010年，

123
00:05:50.547 --> 00:05:54.550
when I received a grant from the  Investigative Reporting Program at U.C. Berkeley,
当时我受邀参加加州大学伯克利分校一个调查报告项目，

124
00:05:54.550 --> 00:05:55.982
and a research assistant and I
我和我的研究助理

125
00:05:55.982 --> 00:05:58.455
put together a database of all terrorism prosecutions
将“9·11”事件发生后十年以来

126
00:05:58.455 --> 00:06:01.458
at the time during  the first decade after 9/11.
所有恐怖主义案件的数据进行了汇总。

127
00:06:01.471 --> 00:06:04.278
And we used the court file to find out whether
我们通过研究法院文件

128
00:06:04.278 --> 00:06:07.701
the defendants had any connections to international terrorist groups,
来调查这些案件的被告是否跟国际恐怖组织有关，

129
00:06:07.701 --> 00:06:09.184
whether an informant was used,
是否有线人牵涉其中，

130
00:06:09.184 --> 00:06:12.326
and whether the informant played the role of an agent provocateur
线人是否扮演了卧底探员的角色，

131
00:06:12.326 --> 00:06:14.193
by providing the means and opportunity.
为他们（被告）出谋划策，创造机会。

132
00:06:14.193 --> 00:06:15.770
And we submitted that to the FBI
我们将这些材料提交给了联邦调查局

133
00:06:15.770 --> 00:06:17.884
and we asked them to respond to our database.
要求他们作出回应。

134
00:06:17.884 --> 00:06:19.841
If they believed there were any errors,
如果他们发现材料有误，

135
00:06:19.841 --> 00:06:22.974
we asked them to tell us what they were and we'd go back and check
可以指出来，我们会再查证，

136
00:06:22.974 --> 00:06:25.202
and they never challenged any of our findings.
但他们从未反驳过我们的任何发现。

137
00:06:24.612 --> 00:06:26.690
Later, I used that data  in a magazine article
之后，我将这些数据用在杂志文章上，

138
00:06:26.690 --> 00:06:28.479
and later in my book,
用在我的书里，

139
00:06:28.449 --> 00:06:30.996
and on appearances on places like CBS and NPR,
哥伦比亚广播公司和国家公共广播电台也用过这些数据，

140
00:06:30.996 --> 00:06:32.903
they were offered that opportunity again
他们再次获得了反驳的机会，

141
00:06:32.903 --> 00:06:35.153
to say, "Trevor Aaronson's  findings are wrong."
大可以说，“特雷弗·阿伦森在胡扯。”

142
00:06:35.153 --> 00:06:37.013
